52 yo male who presented for R TCAR with Dr. Dwivedi. ICU is being consulted for critical care management. Patient was diagnosed with bilateral carotid stenosis in November when he went to the ED after seeing white spots in both eyes. He had become concerned that he had a stroke and that is why he presented to the ED. Patient was admitted to the hospital today after right TCAR. Upon my assessment in PACU, patient was laying supine in the bed. States that his neck was a little sore but manageable. No other active complaints.
